# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# LearnX Social Media Automation — Environment Variables
# Copy this to .env.local and fill in your values
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Supabase ──
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# ── Vercel Cron ──
CRON_SECRET=your-random-secret-string

# ── Meta (Instagram + Facebook + Threads + WhatsApp) ──
# Get these from https://developers.facebook.com
META_APP_ID=your-meta-app-id
META_APP_SECRET=your-meta-app-secret

# ── Twitter/X ──
# Get these from https://developer.twitter.com
# Free tier: 1,500 tweets/month (write-only)

# ── LinkedIn ──
# Get these from https://linkedin.com/developers

# ── Telegram ──
# Create a bot via @BotFather on Telegram
# Create a channel and add your bot as admin

# ── YouTube ──
# Enable YouTube Data API v3 in Google Cloud Console
# https://console.cloud.google.com

# ── Pinterest ──
# Apply at https://developers.pinterest.com

# ── Reddit ──
# Create app at https://reddit.com/prefs/apps

# Note: Individual platform credentials (tokens, keys) are stored
# in the Supabase platform_credentials table, not here.
# Only Supabase + Cron + Meta App credentials go in env vars.
